41
00:01:50,655 --> 00:01:51,954
(1-million-dollar alley sales status)

42
00:01:51,955 --> 00:01:55,664
(1,450 for P burger place, 745 for P restaurant)

43
00:01:55,665 --> 00:01:56,724
(Single Pan House made more.)

44
00:01:56,725 --> 00:01:58,435
- We made more. - We made more.

45
00:01:59,795 --> 00:02:01,565
I think we did better than yesterday.

46
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:04,035
- We beat one, at least. - We beat one, at least.

47
00:02:04,505 --> 00:02:06,205
- Next. - I'm getting scared.

48
00:02:06,435 --> 00:02:07,705
The next restaurant.

49
00:02:08,405 --> 00:02:10,944
(M restaurant and L restaurant...)

50
00:02:10,945 --> 00:02:15,884
(placed 3rd and 4th yesterday.)

51
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:20,015
(1st, bottom, 2nd, 3rd, 4th)

52
00:02:21,085 --> 00:02:22,724
(Single Pan House placed 4th.)

53
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:23,885
We beat only one place.

54
00:02:24,855 --> 00:02:27,054
(Progress to making 1 million dollars a year)

55
00:02:27,055 --> 00:02:28,294
(At 13 percent)

56
00:02:28,295 --> 00:02:31,465
(11,718 euros to go)

57
00:02:31,795 --> 00:02:36,065
(They have to make 19,040 dollars in 6 days.)

58
00:02:36,165 --> 00:02:37,465
I think we can do it.

59
00:02:39,375 --> 00:02:40,435
Yes.

60
00:02:41,705 --> 00:02:43,904
We'll only be open for lunch today.

61
00:02:43,905 --> 00:02:45,545
It's Friday, right?

62
00:02:46,015 --> 00:02:47,614
- It'll be crowded today, right? - So...

63
00:02:47,615 --> 00:02:49,085
(Friday)

64
00:02:50,115 --> 00:02:53,685
(Friday is more special in France.)

65
00:02:54,115 --> 00:02:57,025
(France is known as a paradise for laborers.)

66
00:02:57,455 --> 00:03:00,725
(They work 35 hours a week, which is 4.5 days.)

67
00:03:01,125 --> 00:03:04,295
(Many people stop working on Fridays.)

68
00:03:04,665 --> 00:03:08,405
(Which means their weekend starts on Friday.)

69
00:03:09,035 --> 00:03:11,935
(There are plenty of customers out on their day off.)

70
00:03:12,535 --> 00:03:16,945
(It's the beginning of a busy business day.)

71
00:03:17,105 --> 00:03:19,244
If we can sell soju, we'll make it.

72
00:03:19,245 --> 00:03:20,444
(Chef Paik will snatch the opportunity.)

73
00:03:20,445 --> 00:03:22,384
If we sell drinks today, tomorrow, and Sunday,

74
00:03:22,385 --> 00:03:24,455
I think we will make the goal.

75
00:03:24,685 --> 00:03:25,715
(Planning to make a lot over the weekend)

76
00:03:25,815 --> 00:03:26,954
Okay, let's go.

77
00:03:26,955 --> 00:03:29,225
(Heading for the restaurant with hope)

78
00:03:29,355 --> 00:03:31,355
Let's try it. Let's go.

79
00:03:31,455 --> 00:03:32,795
Let's go!

80
00:03:35,695 --> 00:03:36,924
Come here. Let's have a meeting.

81
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:38,065
(They made it to work.)

82
00:03:38,465 --> 00:03:41,065
(Discussing before a busy Friday)

83
00:03:41,865 --> 00:03:43,164
(What's the strategy?)

84
00:03:43,165 --> 00:03:44,805
Today...

85
00:03:45,505 --> 00:03:48,375
To reiterate, the menu today is stir-fried spicy chicken.

86
00:03:49,275 --> 00:03:50,374
Stir-fried spicy chicken.

87
00:03:50,375 --> 00:03:52,945
(They'll switch the menu to stir-fried spicy chicken.)

88
00:03:53,645 --> 00:03:56,615
(The issue with a pan of pork belly...)

89
00:03:57,085 --> 00:04:00,915
(is that it needs a 1-on-1 care.)

90
00:04:01,225 --> 00:04:05,325
(It's not possible to tend to so many customers.)

91
00:04:05,925 --> 00:04:08,425
(By tending to them less, they can handle more customers.)

92
00:04:09,065 --> 00:04:11,165
(Today's menu: Stir-fried spicy chicken)

93
00:04:11,735 --> 00:04:13,935
(A leading single-pan dish in Korea)

94
00:04:14,635 --> 00:04:17,765
(Stir-fried spicy chicken)

95
00:04:18,235 --> 00:04:20,735
(Its biggest strength is...)

96
00:04:22,045 --> 00:04:23,244
(that it's served fully cooked.)

97
00:04:23,245 --> 00:04:25,674
(No need to help customers grill)

98
00:04:25,675 --> 00:04:29,144
We won't have to tend to the customers as much.

99
00:04:29,145 --> 00:04:30,244
- Okay. - Not with this.

100
00:04:30,245 --> 00:04:32,755
We'll have shorter turnarounds.

101
00:04:33,455 --> 00:04:35,254
We can open up the second floor right away.

102
00:04:35,255 --> 00:04:37,625
(They'll open the 2nd floor to hold more customers!)

103
00:04:38,425 --> 00:04:40,855
(Single Pan House's secret weapon)

104
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:43,925
(The 2nd floor)

105
00:04:44,225 --> 00:04:46,865
(Through the 1st floor and up the stairs...)

106
00:04:47,395 --> 00:04:50,735
(is the 2nd floor with 22 seats!)

107
00:04:51,505 --> 00:04:53,204
(It was closed on days 1 and 2...)

108
00:04:53,205 --> 00:04:55,545
(because they had to serve customers one-on-one.)

109
00:04:56,145 --> 00:04:57,344
(The menu change...)

110
00:04:57,345 --> 00:05:00,175
(allows them to open up the 2nd floor.)

111
00:05:01,315 --> 00:05:03,814
(Friday Sales Strategy)

112
00:05:03,815 --> 00:05:06,214
(Upgrade: Stir-fried spicy chicken)

113
00:05:06,215 --> 00:05:09,185
(Upgrade: Open the 2nd floor)

114
00:05:09,325 --> 00:05:12,295
(Will the two upgrades...)

115
00:05:12,525 --> 00:05:16,595
(lead them to good Friday sales?)

116
00:05:16,695 --> 00:05:18,795
Jang Woo, isn't it time to get the chicken?

117
00:05:19,095 --> 00:05:20,165
I'll be back.

118
00:05:22,035 --> 00:05:24,235
Lyon.

119
00:05:25,505 --> 00:05:26,505
Hello.

120
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:29,174
(He's like a big happy puppy on his walk.)

121
00:05:29,175 --> 00:05:30,575
I met them yesterday too.

122
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:34,515
(On his way to the butcher's to get some chicken)

123
00:05:35,845 --> 00:05:36,885
Hello.

124
00:05:37,445 --> 00:05:38,515
My friend.

125
00:05:38,915 --> 00:05:40,015
Order chicken.

126
00:05:40,615 --> 00:05:41,985
- Call... Chicken. - Chicken, yes.

127
00:05:42,255 --> 00:05:43,485
- Around 10kg. - Yes.

128
00:05:43,585 --> 00:05:45,155
- Around 10kg. - Without the bone?

129
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:48,065
Bone.

130
00:05:48,465 --> 00:05:50,565
(So does he want the bones or not?)

131
00:05:52,165 --> 00:05:56,835
(Deboning)

132
00:05:56,935 --> 00:05:58,504
(Watching)

133
00:05:58,505 --> 00:05:59,735
He's removing the bones.

134
00:06:01,845 --> 00:06:03,744
He asked you, "Without the bone?"

135
00:06:03,745 --> 00:06:05,075
That's why.

136
00:06:05,345 --> 00:06:07,044
Did he? Your English is good.

137
00:06:07,045 --> 00:06:08,544
(Embarrassed)

138
00:06:08,545 --> 00:06:09,744
Didn't he say, "With bone?"

139
00:06:09,745 --> 00:06:10,785
(I thought he said, "With bone.")

140
00:06:11,315 --> 00:06:14,485
(While Jang Woo is waiting for the chicken...)

141
00:06:14,585 --> 00:06:15,585
What's upstairs?

142
00:06:15,586 --> 00:06:17,655
(Meanwhile, the floor manager is...)

143
00:06:17,995 --> 00:06:19,294
There's nothing here.

144
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:20,525
(preparing to open the 2nd floor.)

145
00:06:21,155 --> 00:06:23,265
(Empty)

146
00:06:23,695 --> 00:06:25,465
(Fiddling)

147
00:06:26,065 --> 00:06:27,234
(It's pressing to set up the 2nd floor.)

148
00:06:27,235 --> 00:06:29,405
- Do we only have one torch? - What?

149
00:06:29,765 --> 00:06:32,275
(Pop)

150
00:06:32,505 --> 00:06:34,645
(Climbing up a 2nd time with portable stoves)

151
00:06:35,345 --> 00:06:37,675
(The first set of goods has moved in.)

152
00:06:39,175 --> 00:06:42,015
(Taking some liquid fuel for the stoves)

153
00:06:42,515 --> 00:06:45,554
(Climbing a 3rd time)

154
00:06:45,555 --> 00:06:49,225
(Filling up fuel)

155
00:06:50,285 --> 00:06:53,495
(This is not a replay.)

156
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:57,825
(Wiping the tables clean)

157
00:06:58,635 --> 00:07:00,365
(Climbing a 5th and 6th time with dishes)

158
00:07:00,695 --> 00:07:04,065
(7th: Cup, 8th: Tongs, 9th: Lighter, 10th: Stoves)

159
00:07:04,875 --> 00:07:08,675
(Climbing up to the 2nd floor nonstop)

160
00:07:09,305 --> 00:07:12,715
(The 2nd floor is filling up.)

161
00:07:13,175 --> 00:07:15,085
(Before)

162
00:07:16,085 --> 00:07:19,185
(After)

163
00:07:20,055 --> 00:07:22,685
(Proud)

164
00:07:23,455 --> 00:07:25,054
(That's when the part-timers arrive.)

165
00:07:25,055 --> 00:07:26,595
- Hello. - Hello.

166
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:28,964
(Chicken Jang Woo follows.)

167
00:07:28,965 --> 00:07:29,995
I'm back.

168
00:07:30,965 --> 00:07:32,595
- Is the chicken here? - Yes.

169
00:07:33,435 --> 00:07:34,465
Hand them to me.

170
00:07:34,935 --> 00:07:38,875
(It's exciting to unbox the chicken.)

171
00:07:42,805 --> 00:07:44,945
There are still feathers on this.

172
00:07:46,145 --> 00:07:49,984
(Unshaven)

173
00:07:49,985 --> 00:07:51,954
Gosh, it has feathers.

174
00:07:51,955 --> 00:07:53,215
(It's his first time seeing feathers on a chicken.)

175
00:07:53,655 --> 00:07:55,054
The meat looks delicious,

176
00:07:55,055 --> 00:07:57,055
but they still need some cleaning up.

177
00:07:57,625 --> 00:07:58,855
I'll remove the feathers.

178
00:08:00,595 --> 00:08:03,295
(Here comes Si Yoon, the master of organizing.)

179
00:08:08,935 --> 00:08:12,034
(He's having a hard time while working with bare hands.)

180
00:08:12,035 --> 00:08:13,775
(Staring)

181
00:08:14,305 --> 00:08:17,044
(He found some kitchen tweezers.)

182
00:08:17,045 --> 00:08:19,075
(Passing the tweezers)

183
00:08:19,645 --> 00:08:22,315
(Trying again with new equipment)

184
00:08:27,685 --> 00:08:30,385
(The complex surgery went on for a long time.)

185
00:08:30,985 --> 00:08:33,325
- Is it done? - Yes, I'm done.

186
00:08:35,865 --> 00:08:38,365
(Clean)

187
00:08:41,335 --> 00:08:45,005
(Si Yoon prepared the chicken swiftly.)

188
00:08:46,205 --> 00:08:49,645
(Start cooking stir-fried spicy chicken)

189
00:08:52,845 --> 00:08:57,114
(Actually, there is a sad story...)

190
00:08:57,115 --> 00:09:01,155
(behind the stir-fried spicy chicken.)

191
00:09:02,955 --> 00:09:06,255
(It happened 4 days ago.)

192
00:09:07,155 --> 00:09:10,465
(Testing before opening)

193
00:09:10,665 --> 00:09:12,964
- Is that stir-fried spicy chicken? - Yes, chicken.

194
00:09:12,965 --> 00:09:16,165
(They worked hard to make stir-fried spicy chicken.)

195
00:09:16,805 --> 00:09:18,404
(It was made with the sauce we all know.)

196
00:09:18,405 --> 00:09:19,975
- Isn't it amazing? - It looks like... Wait.

197
00:09:20,605 --> 00:09:22,175
It's going to be so good when cooked.

198
00:09:23,305 --> 00:09:28,545
(They attempted to bake it in large quantities.)

199
00:09:29,185 --> 00:09:31,855
(10 minutes later)

200
00:09:32,515 --> 00:09:35,525
(20 minutes later)

201
00:09:36,025 --> 00:09:41,024
(Checking the oven time to time)

202
00:09:41,025 --> 00:09:43,065
(But...)

203
00:09:43,525 --> 00:09:44,665
What is this?

204
00:09:46,335 --> 00:09:47,394
No way.

205
00:09:47,395 --> 00:09:49,535
(What happened to the chicken?)

206
00:09:49,835 --> 00:09:51,165
Why? Are they all burnt?

207
00:09:51,505 --> 00:09:52,534
Are they burnt?

208
00:09:52,535 --> 00:09:54,774
(They are burnt.)

209
00:09:54,775 --> 00:09:56,804
- Gosh. - It happened in a flash.

210
00:09:56,805 --> 00:09:58,245
In the blink of an eye.

211
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:01,515
I had a mental breakdown then.

212
00:10:03,745 --> 00:10:07,485
It's supposed to be connected to the tap.

213
00:10:07,615 --> 00:10:09,355
But the water isn't running right now.

214
00:10:11,025 --> 00:10:13,125
It would steam and cook well with water.

215
00:10:13,295 --> 00:10:14,394
There was no steam.

216
00:10:14,395 --> 00:10:15,465
(The oven wasn't connected to the tap.)

217
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:20,295
(It's not possible to cook it with the regular sauce...)

218
00:10:20,395 --> 00:10:21,704
(because it burns before the meat is cooked.)

219
00:10:21,705 --> 00:10:23,905
It was burnt because there was no moisture.

220
00:10:25,535 --> 00:10:29,205
(They must use the oven since the kitchen is so small.)

221
00:10:29,475 --> 00:10:33,545
(How can this be resolved?)

222
00:10:33,815 --> 00:10:35,615
As for the chicken,

223
00:10:35,915 --> 00:10:38,114
it will be stir-fried spicy chicken...

224
00:10:38,115 --> 00:10:39,455
but saucy.

225
00:10:40,685 --> 00:10:43,985
It'll be between a stir-fry and a braised spicy chicken.

226
00:10:44,255 --> 00:10:47,895
The sauce will be similar to a braised spicy chicken.

227
00:10:49,565 --> 00:10:52,565
(The key to the new recipe...)

228
00:10:53,765 --> 00:10:56,965
(is water!)

229
00:10:57,605 --> 00:11:00,575
(Filling the containers with water)

230
00:11:00,705 --> 00:11:02,545
- There is a lot of water. - We need a lot.

231
00:11:03,505 --> 00:11:04,875
It will burn otherwise.

232
00:11:05,745 --> 00:11:08,345
(Adding sweet and salty tastes)

233
00:11:08,715 --> 00:11:11,315
(Also, onions)

234
00:11:12,285 --> 00:11:17,255
(Like braised spicy chicken, the meat goes into the water.)

235
00:11:18,695 --> 00:11:23,795
(The water will prevent it from burning.)

236
00:11:24,195 --> 00:11:27,735
(A braised spicy chicken style stir-fried spicy chicken!)

237
00:11:28,765 --> 00:11:31,975
(Grunting)

238
00:11:33,575 --> 00:11:37,805
(Pre-cooking a full container)

239
00:11:38,515 --> 00:11:42,715
(Making the sauce in the meantime)

240
00:11:44,385 --> 00:11:47,655
(A big scoop of spicy gochujang)

241
00:11:48,215 --> 00:11:52,055
(Dark soy sauce, chicken stock, soy sauce, doenjang)

242
00:11:53,425 --> 00:11:55,525
- Bring the chicken. - Chicken?

243
00:11:57,225 --> 00:11:58,225
(Yes!)

244
00:11:59,395 --> 00:12:03,065
(If the top is turning brown,)

245
00:12:03,505 --> 00:12:08,075
(it's time to add the sauce.)

246
00:12:09,445 --> 00:12:12,914
(Flip the meat once)

247
00:12:12,915 --> 00:12:14,844
- Should I put this in? - Yes.

248
00:12:14,845 --> 00:12:19,385
(Heading back to the oven a 2nd time)

249
00:12:21,155 --> 00:12:25,255
(Once baked with the sauce...)

250
00:12:25,555 --> 00:12:26,694
Stir-fried spicy chicken.

251
00:12:26,695 --> 00:12:30,265
(The result is...)

252
00:12:32,165 --> 00:12:33,464
The chicken looks so good.

253
00:12:33,465 --> 00:12:35,835
(It was cooked just right.)

254
00:12:37,405 --> 00:12:41,435
(Once ordered, it's stir-fried with the sauce.)

255
00:12:42,305 --> 00:12:44,004
(It will be boiled down in a pan!)

256
00:12:44,005 --> 00:12:45,374
That smells fantastic.

257
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:47,175
(It will be boiled down in a pan!)

258
00:12:47,575 --> 00:12:50,985
(And beside the stir-fried spicy chicken...)

259
00:12:51,685 --> 00:12:55,125
(are all kinds of toppings.)

260
00:12:55,525 --> 00:12:58,855
(First up is a spicy chicken's best friend.)

261
00:12:58,895 --> 00:13:00,394
Toppings?

262
00:13:00,395 --> 00:13:02,865
I think tteokbokki is always welcomed.

263
00:13:03,265 --> 00:13:06,465
(Adding red sauce to it to match the chicken)

264
00:13:08,705 --> 00:13:11,974
It's nice to braise it in the same sauce,

265
00:13:11,975 --> 00:13:13,534
although we might not have an abundance of it.

266
00:13:13,535 --> 00:13:14,905
(Braised potato in the same sauce...)

267
00:13:15,475 --> 00:13:18,305
(It would be a pity not to have udon noodles.)

268
00:13:19,045 --> 00:13:20,875
(Lastly, the key to stir-fried spicy chicken)

269
00:13:21,645 --> 00:13:24,285
We should top it with cheese at the end.

270
00:13:28,215 --> 00:13:31,754
Some might have never had cheese with spicy sauce before.

271
00:13:31,755 --> 00:13:33,295
They go really well together.

272
00:13:34,825 --> 00:13:38,025
(It controls the spiciness.)

273
00:13:39,295 --> 00:13:44,065
(Its best friend, cheese, will join in.)

274
00:13:45,105 --> 00:13:49,475
(A pan of stir-fried spicy chicken is ready!)

275
00:13:50,845 --> 00:13:53,875
(In preparation for a busy Friday,)

276
00:13:54,515 --> 00:13:57,945
(they will introduce stir-fried spicy chicken.)

277
00:13:58,285 --> 00:14:01,555
(How many customers will they get to bring in?)

278
00:14:01,615 --> 00:14:03,024
We're open!

279
00:14:03,025 --> 00:14:06,395
(Current time: 12pm)

280
00:14:11,895 --> 00:14:16,205
(Someone is approaching the restaurant.)

281
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:19,505
- Welcome! - Welcome!

282
00:14:19,835 --> 00:14:22,205
(His company is joining.)

283
00:14:22,605 --> 00:14:25,215
(It's a family of 3.)

284
00:14:25,445 --> 00:14:27,075
Would you like to sit on the terrace or inside?

285
00:14:27,275 --> 00:14:28,784
- Inside, please. - Inside?

286
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:30,415
- Follow me. - Thank you.

287
00:14:31,715 --> 00:14:32,715
Come on.

288
00:14:32,785 --> 00:14:35,725
(The first chicken customers are sitting down.)

289
00:14:36,185 --> 00:14:38,385
(Now that we have customers...)

290
00:14:39,155 --> 00:14:41,055
Bring out the chicken.

291
00:14:42,095 --> 00:14:44,765
(Warming)

292
00:14:45,865 --> 00:14:48,635
(Overflowing)

293
00:14:49,165 --> 00:14:51,805
(Clenching teeth)

294
00:14:52,505 --> 00:14:55,575
(His eyes are on Jang Woo.)

295
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:58,245
(Walking as gently as possible)

296
00:14:58,615 --> 00:15:00,844
Lower yourself. Bend down.

297
00:15:00,845 --> 00:15:02,444
(Setting it down with a squat and a red face)

298
00:15:02,445 --> 00:15:03,445
Please...

299
00:15:03,845 --> 00:15:04,915
All right.

300
00:15:06,185 --> 00:15:09,425
(It landed safely without a spill.)

301
00:15:10,225 --> 00:15:11,225
I'm going to start!

302
00:15:11,895 --> 00:15:13,995
Put it over here where they can see it.

303
00:15:14,195 --> 00:15:15,195
Okay.

304
00:15:15,196 --> 00:15:16,925
(Gently placing)

305
00:15:17,695 --> 00:15:20,395
Let's make sure they can see this for the time being.

306
00:15:20,935 --> 00:15:22,035
Here we go.

307
00:15:22,665 --> 00:15:24,735
The customers can enjoy watching it for now.

308
00:15:26,305 --> 00:15:27,405
Enjoy.

309
00:15:28,035 --> 00:15:29,375
Enjoy it with your eyes.

310
00:15:30,005 --> 00:15:32,315
(The stir-fried spicy chicken is being displayed in the window.)

311
00:15:33,115 --> 00:15:35,945
(Halting)

312
00:15:36,845 --> 00:15:38,714
(This passerby is interested.)

313
00:15:38,715 --> 00:15:39,915
Hello, Sir.

314
00:15:41,255 --> 00:15:44,485
(A passing couple...)

315
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,324
(also takes a peek at the chicken.)

316
00:15:47,325 --> 00:15:48,325
Hello.

317
00:15:48,495 --> 00:15:49,824
(Stopping in front of the restaurant)

318
00:15:49,825 --> 00:15:50,894
Hello.

319
00:15:50,895 --> 00:15:52,364
Is there a table for two?

320
00:15:52,365 --> 00:15:55,605
Yes. Would you like to sit inside or outside?

321
00:15:55,865 --> 00:15:58,005
- Welcome! - Welcome!

322
00:16:04,775 --> 00:16:06,545
It looks spicy.

323
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:12,915
(They head inside right away.)

324
00:16:13,115 --> 00:16:14,185
- Hello. - Come on.

325
00:16:15,625 --> 00:16:17,655
- They came yesterday. - Yesterday.

326
00:16:17,825 --> 00:16:20,595
We met yesterday.

327
00:16:21,495 --> 00:16:24,525
(This customer visited yesterday with his wife.)

328
00:16:24,965 --> 00:16:28,635
(He had a pan of pork belly.)

329
00:16:29,365 --> 00:16:31,765
(He's visiting with a friend today.)

330
00:16:33,135 --> 00:16:34,535
Outside or inside?

331
00:16:34,875 --> 00:16:36,445
- Inside. - Inside.

332
00:16:38,005 --> 00:16:40,144
(First customers to enter the 2nd floor)

333
00:16:40,145 --> 00:16:41,615
(Following closely)

334
00:16:42,215 --> 00:16:45,654
(Following the couple,)

335
00:16:45,655 --> 00:16:48,185
(there is also a solo customer.)

336
00:16:48,725 --> 00:16:51,685
(The 2nd floor is in business!)

337
00:16:52,495 --> 00:16:55,365
(Customers are busy ordering on the 1st floor.)

338
00:16:55,495 --> 00:16:56,764
There is only one menu.

339
00:16:56,765 --> 00:16:58,495
Yes. It's great.

340
00:17:00,635 --> 00:17:03,505
(2 pans of stir-fried spicy chicken, 2 desserts, 2 beers)

341
00:17:04,935 --> 00:17:05,935
Hello.

342
00:17:05,936 --> 00:17:07,734
Do you need me to explain?

343
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:09,074
- Yes. - Yes, please.

344
00:17:09,075 --> 00:17:11,574
Do you know anything about Korean food?

345
00:17:11,575 --> 00:17:14,414
My daughter actually wants to visit Korea.

346
00:17:14,415 --> 00:17:16,944
She has a lot of interest in the country.

347
00:17:16,945 --> 00:17:20,155
She's preparing a presentation on Korea at school.

348
00:17:20,185 --> 00:17:23,485
(Lena is visiting to do a research on Korea.)

349
00:17:23,655 --> 00:17:25,954
Okay. We will order everything.

350
00:17:25,955 --> 00:17:27,394
(3 pans of stir-fried spicy chicken, 3 desserts, 2 water,)

351
00:17:27,395 --> 00:17:28,625
(2 sparkling water, 1 grapefruit soju)

352
00:17:29,065 --> 00:17:32,095
She is allergic to peanuts.

353
00:17:32,135 --> 00:17:35,535
(Special note: The daughter is allergic to peanuts.)

354
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:39,134
As for the order that just came in,

355
00:17:39,135 --> 00:17:42,674
the daughter is allergic to peanuts. Please be careful.

356
00:17:42,675 --> 00:17:44,805
- Okay! - Thank you.

357
00:17:46,015 --> 00:17:47,214
Okay, the first order.

358
00:17:47,215 --> 00:17:49,545
(Cooking the first order)

359
00:17:50,015 --> 00:17:54,185
(Picking a big piece of chicken)

360
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:58,485
- Pour some sauce. - Here is some sauce.

361
00:17:58,695 --> 00:18:03,165
(Adding enough sauce)

362
00:18:04,025 --> 00:18:05,765
It's clearly good chicken.

363
00:18:06,865 --> 00:18:10,005
(Cutting it into bite sizes)

364
00:18:10,205 --> 00:18:14,105
(Chopped bell peppers and green onions...)

365
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:18,875
(are thrown on top of the chicken.)

366
00:18:19,945 --> 00:18:23,015
(Boiling it down in a single pan)

367
00:18:23,715 --> 00:18:27,685
(Topping time follows.)

368
00:18:27,785 --> 00:18:29,185
That's good. Put potatoes on one side.

369
00:18:30,785 --> 00:18:32,555
(Pre-prepared potatoes are going in.)

370
00:18:33,055 --> 00:18:35,625
(A heap)

371
00:18:36,025 --> 00:18:37,095
Potatoes and rice cakes?

372
00:18:38,495 --> 00:18:41,365
(A heap of rice cakes)

373
00:18:41,735 --> 00:18:46,075
(Lastly, a spread of Mozarella cheese)

374
00:18:54,715 --> 00:19:00,355
(A pan of stir-fried spicy chicken is ready.)

375
00:19:00,855 --> 00:19:01,914
Number two can go out.

376
00:19:01,915 --> 00:19:03,225
- Number two? - Yes.

377
00:19:07,025 --> 00:19:09,364
(2 pans of stir-fried spicy chicken)

378
00:19:09,365 --> 00:19:12,495
(Gulping)

379
00:19:12,565 --> 00:19:13,894
(John is in guide mode.)

380
00:19:13,895 --> 00:19:15,335
This is stir-fried spicy chicken.

381
00:19:15,935 --> 00:19:19,075
You can have cheese or rice cakes with it.

382
00:19:19,505 --> 00:19:21,135
It's very good.

383
00:19:22,405 --> 00:19:26,275
(The key to stir-fried spicy chicken is cheese.)

384
00:19:26,845 --> 00:19:30,715
(Have it with the chicken when it melts.)

385
00:19:30,945 --> 00:19:32,884
Please enjoy.

386
00:19:32,885 --> 00:19:33,984
- Thank you. - Thank you.

387
00:19:33,985 --> 00:19:35,625
(It's simpler to explain than a pan of pork belly.)

388
00:19:35,925 --> 00:19:37,355
Wait.

389
00:19:38,225 --> 00:19:40,825
(Picture time is a must before eating.)

390
00:19:41,125 --> 00:19:43,825
(He's used to it.)

391
00:19:44,125 --> 00:19:46,635
Sorry for making you wait, but it looks so good.

392
00:19:49,505 --> 00:19:50,535
My goodness.

393
00:19:50,905 --> 00:19:52,575
Wait, do we have to mix it?

394
00:19:52,635 --> 00:19:54,274
No, no.

395
00:19:54,275 --> 00:19:55,875
(Firm)

396
00:19:57,305 --> 00:20:00,075
Are you going to eat it like that? I'm going to take a bit.

397
00:20:02,115 --> 00:20:07,085
(Taking a little of everything onto her plate)

398
00:20:12,155 --> 00:20:13,855
(Delicious!)

399
00:20:15,355 --> 00:20:17,725
It's not as spicy as I thought.

400
00:20:17,865 --> 00:20:19,665
They must have made it mild for us.

401
00:20:23,365 --> 00:20:24,635
- Is it good? - Yes.

402
00:20:29,005 --> 00:20:31,245
(The cheese has melted.)

403
00:20:36,715 --> 00:20:40,455
(Taking a bite of chicken with some cheese)

404
00:20:40,755 --> 00:20:43,155
This is the good stuff.

405
00:20:43,425 --> 00:20:45,895
(Sizzling)

406
00:20:50,965 --> 00:20:52,025
Gosh.

407
00:20:52,935 --> 00:20:54,665
The cheese is amazing.

408
00:20:55,805 --> 00:20:57,905
(John takes notice of them.)

409
00:20:59,005 --> 00:21:01,275
Chef, could you pass me some more cheese?

410
00:21:03,745 --> 00:21:06,775
(Cheese topping on the house)

411
00:21:09,915 --> 00:21:10,915
It's perfect.

412
00:21:11,285 --> 00:21:12,315
Thank you.

413
00:21:15,985 --> 00:21:18,585
Do you grill the cheese in Korea too?

414
00:21:19,225 --> 00:21:20,355
- Yes. - Really?

415
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:23,125
- Bigger... - Thank you.

416
00:21:23,265 --> 00:21:25,425
(We mix it on a bigger grill.)

417
00:21:26,035 --> 00:21:28,735
(Scraping the cheese off)

418
00:21:28,865 --> 00:21:30,535
A bit of the cheese was burnt.

419
00:21:33,305 --> 00:21:34,475
I didn't see it before.

420
00:21:38,805 --> 00:21:40,515
This is the Korean fondue.

421
00:21:40,675 --> 00:21:44,815
Yes, just like how the fondue cheese burns at the end.

422
00:21:45,445 --> 00:21:49,155
You eat that with an egg at the very end.

423
00:21:51,955 --> 00:21:55,595
(Fondue)

424
00:21:56,595 --> 00:22:01,295
(A French and Swiss cuisine in which you dip food in cheese)

425
00:22:02,035 --> 00:22:05,035
(It requires you to heat up cheese.)

426
00:22:05,265 --> 00:22:08,705
(The cheese scorches at the end.)

427
00:22:09,475 --> 00:22:14,175
(When eating the scorched cheese,)

428
00:22:14,845 --> 00:22:19,015
(you can add a raw egg.)

429
00:22:19,685 --> 00:22:26,255
(Eating the melted cheese with an egg is very popular!)

430
00:22:26,795 --> 00:22:29,224
(We all love scorched cheese.)

431
00:22:29,225 --> 00:22:30,265
Number two?

432
00:22:31,925 --> 00:22:32,965
Three people?

433
00:22:36,505 --> 00:22:40,535
(Here is a pan of stir-fried spicy chicken.)

434
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:43,475
Excuse me.

435
00:22:44,105 --> 00:22:46,845
(3 servings of stir-fried spicy chicken)

436
00:22:53,655 --> 00:22:56,425
(Taking a piece of chicken...)

437
00:22:57,085 --> 00:22:59,855
(to hand to his daughter first)

438
00:23:00,925 --> 00:23:03,024
I wonder if it's too spicy.

439
00:23:03,025 --> 00:23:06,565
(Worried about the spiciness before trying)

440
00:23:07,035 --> 00:23:10,605
(The mother is taking a cautious bite.)

441
00:23:11,305 --> 00:23:14,905
(She follows suit.)

442
00:23:16,675 --> 00:23:19,344
The sauce isn't too spicy.

443
00:23:19,345 --> 00:23:20,674
It's not spicy at all.

444
00:23:20,675 --> 00:23:21,715
(Coughing)

445
00:23:21,845 --> 00:23:24,415
(It must be spicy for Lena.)

446
00:23:24,885 --> 00:23:26,814
(Lena's notes on her presentation on Korea)

447
00:23:26,815 --> 00:23:29,855
(1. Stir-fried spicy chicken is spicy.)

448
00:23:30,385 --> 00:23:33,625
(Yu Ri notices a customer who finds the chicken spicy.)

449
00:23:34,395 --> 00:23:38,395
(For her customer who can't eat spicy dishes...)

450
00:23:39,995 --> 00:23:41,565
I recommend you this combination.

451
00:23:43,535 --> 00:23:44,634
(A lot of cheese)

452
00:23:44,635 --> 00:23:46,405
My goodness.

453
00:23:50,405 --> 00:23:52,645
(It won't come off.)

454
00:23:53,845 --> 00:23:55,244
Thank you.

455
00:23:55,245 --> 00:23:56,245
(A helping hand)

456
00:23:56,385 --> 00:23:59,715
(Trying the chicken with cheese as recommended)

457
00:24:06,395 --> 00:24:10,865
(She's now trying cheese with a rice cake.)

458
00:24:11,865 --> 00:24:15,265
(Cheese is the best at controlling spiciness.)

459
00:24:15,765 --> 00:24:18,035
(Eat it with melted cheese.)

460
00:24:21,535 --> 00:24:24,905
(The best combination with spicy tastes)

461
00:24:26,115 --> 00:24:27,744
(1. Stir-fried spicy chicken is spicy.)

462
00:24:27,745 --> 00:24:31,615
(But it's not spicy with cheese.)

463
00:24:32,455 --> 00:24:35,655
(Current time: 12:40pm, 40 minutes past opening)

464
00:24:36,255 --> 00:24:42,365
(Rue Merciere on a Friday)

465
00:24:45,225 --> 00:24:48,695
(It's different from a Korean Friday.)

466
00:24:49,205 --> 00:24:52,065
(Since French people do not work on Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays,)

467
00:24:52,775 --> 00:24:55,635
(their weekends start on Fridays!)

468
00:25:01,415 --> 00:25:06,485
(Today, there are more families out with their children.)

469
00:25:07,515 --> 00:25:10,885
(Single Pan House is no exception.)

470
00:25:11,555 --> 00:25:14,295
(Here's a family visiting.)

471
00:25:14,695 --> 00:25:16,494
(Entering the restaurant)

472
00:25:16,495 --> 00:25:17,795
- Hello. - Welcome.

473
00:25:18,025 --> 00:25:19,095
Welcome.

474
00:25:19,595 --> 00:25:22,334
Could we leave our stroller somewhere?

475
00:25:22,335 --> 00:25:24,605
Do we have space for a stroller?

476
00:25:24,905 --> 00:25:26,734
- There... - Yes, they can put it there.

477
00:25:26,735 --> 00:25:28,074
- On the inside. - Yes.

478
00:25:28,075 --> 00:25:29,274
They have to go around.

479
00:25:29,275 --> 00:25:31,274
Hello.

480
00:25:31,275 --> 00:25:32,875
It's a baby.

481
00:25:33,715 --> 00:25:34,915
A newborn.

482
00:25:35,475 --> 00:25:37,485
A newborn just came in.

483
00:25:38,185 --> 00:25:39,254
The baby is sleeping.

484
00:25:39,255 --> 00:25:40,584
(The baby is getting the staff's attention.)

485
00:25:40,585 --> 00:25:41,655
Such a young baby.

486
00:25:46,795 --> 00:25:50,395
(The baby is the youngest customer at Single Pan House.)

487
00:25:52,065 --> 00:25:55,565
(Here comes another stroller.)

488
00:25:56,235 --> 00:25:58,705
(Heading straight for Single Pan House)

489
00:25:58,865 --> 00:26:00,274
- There are two more people joining. - Okay.

490
00:26:00,275 --> 00:26:01,535
- It's three plus a baby. - Okay.

491
00:26:02,745 --> 00:26:05,875
(Guiding her to the wooden bench)

492
00:26:06,245 --> 00:26:07,715
- Okay, thank you. - No problem.

493
00:26:08,315 --> 00:26:11,915
(Sitting on the bench with her child)

494
00:26:12,415 --> 00:26:17,585
(A moment later)

495
00:26:18,585 --> 00:26:20,554
- Hello. - Can we sit over there?

496
00:26:20,555 --> 00:26:22,095
Yes, go ahead.

497
00:26:23,565 --> 00:26:27,435
(It's the 3rd table with a stroller.)

498
00:26:30,335 --> 00:26:31,505
Peekaboo.

499
00:26:33,875 --> 00:26:38,205
(There are many babies here since it's Friday.)

500
00:26:38,575 --> 00:26:41,115
(Wiggling)

501
00:26:48,185 --> 00:26:49,784
(Spitting)

502
00:26:49,785 --> 00:26:51,025
It's just a potato.

503
00:26:53,525 --> 00:26:56,665
(Refusing while crossing her legs)

504
00:26:58,265 --> 00:27:00,794
(Meanwhile in the hall)

505
00:27:00,795 --> 00:27:01,864
- Also, John. - Yes?

506
00:27:01,865 --> 00:27:03,835
We shouldn't forget.

507
00:27:04,235 --> 00:27:05,634
Bibimbap... No, I mean...

508
00:27:05,635 --> 00:27:07,975
- Right, we have to do this. - We must talk about it.

509
00:27:08,575 --> 00:27:12,615
(All the floor staff have gathered.)

510
00:27:13,045 --> 00:27:14,045
So...

511
00:27:14,046 --> 00:27:15,774
(They're making something in a circle.)

512
00:27:15,775 --> 00:27:16,845
Like this?

513
00:27:17,985 --> 00:27:18,985
It's hot.

514
00:27:19,685 --> 00:27:20,955
- Is it hot, John? - Yes.

515
00:27:21,355 --> 00:27:25,124
We should tell them to be careful.

516
00:27:25,125 --> 00:27:26,425
Do we go like this...

517
00:27:26,925 --> 00:27:28,455
- In their mouth? - and feed them?

518
00:27:30,295 --> 00:27:31,595
What do we do?

519
00:27:32,695 --> 00:27:34,335
We have to do this, right?

520
00:27:36,765 --> 00:27:39,405
- It looks good. - It's going to take all day.

521
00:27:39,705 --> 00:27:41,775
We have to grill for them too.

522
00:27:42,075 --> 00:27:43,604
Our arms are going to be sore.

523
00:27:43,605 --> 00:27:44,675
(This is what they're preparing.)

524
00:27:45,545 --> 00:27:48,975
(Self-made rice balls)

525
00:27:49,515 --> 00:27:52,714
(When you eat pork belly,)

526
00:27:52,715 --> 00:27:55,925
(you have to have fried rice.)

527
00:27:56,455 --> 00:27:59,695
(With every spicy red sauce,)

528
00:28:00,225 --> 00:28:04,395
(you have to have rice balls.)

529
00:28:04,925 --> 00:28:08,965
(The customers must make them on their own.)

530
00:28:09,365 --> 00:28:11,735
(100 percent handmade)

531
00:28:13,435 --> 00:28:16,305
(It will soften the spiciness of the stir-fried spicy chicken.)

532
00:28:17,575 --> 00:28:21,175
(Self-made rice balls are coming.)

533
00:28:22,885 --> 00:28:24,244
Good.

534
00:28:24,245 --> 00:28:25,815
(Rice balls)

535
00:28:26,255 --> 00:28:27,385
I'll be able to mix it well, right?

536
00:28:27,485 --> 00:28:28,814
(Will it be okay?)

537
00:28:28,815 --> 00:28:29,885
It should be okay.

538
00:28:31,025 --> 00:28:35,495
(They're nervous before serving the first bowl.)

539
00:28:35,895 --> 00:28:38,225
Will you come around with me? Shall we give them one each?

540
00:28:38,395 --> 00:28:40,335
We need to be brave.

541
00:28:41,065 --> 00:28:44,335
- How about now? - Please demonstrate for them.

542
00:28:49,205 --> 00:28:50,274
There is nowhere to put it.

543
00:28:50,275 --> 00:28:52,275
(Rice ball demonstrators are here.)

544
00:28:52,575 --> 00:28:55,044
This is a gift.

545
00:28:55,045 --> 00:28:56,215
- A gift? - Yes.

546
00:28:56,315 --> 00:28:57,784
(Passing over plastic gloves)

547
00:28:57,785 --> 00:28:59,315
This is yours.

548
00:29:00,785 --> 00:29:02,885
This is your right.

549
00:29:02,925 --> 00:29:04,624
Follow me.

550
00:29:04,625 --> 00:29:05,724
- This? - Yes.

551
00:29:05,725 --> 00:29:07,125
Okay, great.

552
00:29:07,655 --> 00:29:10,525
(Mixing)

553
00:29:13,935 --> 00:29:18,565
This is self... Self rice.

554
00:29:19,475 --> 00:29:20,475
Rice balls.

555
00:29:21,475 --> 00:29:23,305
How do we explain it?

556
00:29:23,975 --> 00:29:24,975
Rocks.

557
00:29:27,315 --> 00:29:28,414
Like...

558
00:29:28,415 --> 00:29:31,785
(Their explanation is too rough.)

559
00:29:32,285 --> 00:29:34,484
(When you see a red dish,)

560
00:29:34,485 --> 00:29:37,855
(you think of rice balls.)

561
00:29:38,655 --> 00:29:39,725
(Like so)

562
00:29:42,355 --> 00:29:43,424
(And then you eat it!)

563
00:29:43,425 --> 00:29:44,625
In one bite.

564
00:29:45,265 --> 00:29:47,765
You try.

565
00:29:48,265 --> 00:29:50,805
- I want to try. - Okay.

566
00:29:53,005 --> 00:29:54,074
- Like this? - Yes.

567
00:29:54,075 --> 00:29:55,675
- Okay. - Yes.

568
00:29:56,145 --> 00:29:57,875
- Yes. Good. - Very good.

569
00:29:59,645 --> 00:30:01,545
My goodness.

570
00:30:01,875 --> 00:30:04,585
(Round)

571
00:30:06,215 --> 00:30:07,455
I'll eat this one.

572
00:30:11,385 --> 00:30:12,455
Really good.

573
00:30:12,795 --> 00:30:13,925
I recommend this.

574
00:30:14,125 --> 00:30:15,894
- Dip it. - With this also?

575
00:30:15,895 --> 00:30:17,794
Yes. Up to you.

576
00:30:17,795 --> 00:30:19,295
Yes. Dip it.

577
00:30:19,735 --> 00:30:22,464
- Enjoy. - Enjoy.

578
00:30:22,465 --> 00:30:24,005
(Something huge has passed.)

579
00:30:24,565 --> 00:30:25,805
What a demonstration.

580
00:30:26,705 --> 00:30:28,904
I'm impressed to see them eat it.

581
00:30:28,905 --> 00:30:30,744
We somehow explained to them with our poor English.

582
00:30:30,745 --> 00:30:31,745
(Mission accomplished)

583
00:30:33,475 --> 00:30:35,245
We should take English lessons during our breaks.

584
00:30:37,745 --> 00:30:41,855
(They continue to serve rice balls.)

585
00:30:43,325 --> 00:30:46,195
(The glove is too big for her hand.)

586
00:30:46,295 --> 00:30:48,625
You have to mix all the ingredients.

587
00:30:49,155 --> 00:30:51,595
Then you turn them into small balls.

588
00:30:51,995 --> 00:30:54,595
(Mixing)

589
00:30:55,035 --> 00:30:56,564
(Lena's notes on her presentation on Korea)

590
00:30:56,565 --> 00:31:00,005
(2. Make rice into balls?)

591
00:31:00,135 --> 00:31:03,145
(Making a rice ball)

592
00:31:04,745 --> 00:31:05,745
Here.

593
00:31:06,375 --> 00:31:07,445
Did you see that?

594
00:31:09,315 --> 00:31:10,445
Can I eat it with my hand?

595
00:31:12,615 --> 00:31:14,754
(Hesitating)

596
00:31:14,755 --> 00:31:15,755
Try it.

597
00:31:16,225 --> 00:31:17,454
(Taking a look)

598
00:31:17,455 --> 00:31:20,525
(Going into her mouth)

599
00:31:21,655 --> 00:31:22,725
(Eyebrows rising)

600
00:31:24,725 --> 00:31:26,165
- Can I make another? - Sure.

601
00:31:28,965 --> 00:31:30,134
(2. Make rice into balls?)

602
00:31:30,135 --> 00:31:35,135
(It tastes so good!)

603
00:31:38,845 --> 00:31:40,915
They're good at making rice balls.

604
00:31:41,315 --> 00:31:43,385
- They're working hard. - I'm hungry.

605
00:31:44,445 --> 00:31:45,885
They're having fun.

606
00:31:47,385 --> 00:31:48,785
They ate it all.

607
00:31:49,785 --> 00:31:50,825
(Scraping)

608
00:31:52,085 --> 00:31:53,095
(Scraping)

609
00:31:56,325 --> 00:32:00,635
(The other tables cleared their pans too.)

610
00:32:00,835 --> 00:32:02,465
We served generously, and they finished it.

611
00:32:03,005 --> 00:32:04,465
Things are looking good today.

612
00:32:05,465 --> 00:32:06,505
It's looking good.

613
00:32:08,035 --> 00:32:11,975
(It will finish on a good note with a sweet dessert.)

614
00:32:12,375 --> 00:32:16,185
(Single Pan House's dessert: Hwajeon)

615
00:32:16,845 --> 00:32:19,415
(It's pan-fried in oil to make it soft.)

616
00:32:21,785 --> 00:32:24,825
(It's coated with sweet honey.)

617
00:32:25,155 --> 00:32:27,825
(There are jujube pieces in various shapes.)

618
00:32:29,025 --> 00:32:31,695
(Decorated with edible flowers)

619
00:32:32,525 --> 00:32:35,195
(A tasty and stylish K-dessert)

620
00:32:36,465 --> 00:32:37,634
Two desserts.

621
00:32:37,635 --> 00:32:39,005
(Heading straight to a table)

622
00:32:40,905 --> 00:32:44,645
(Here are your hwajeons.)

623
00:32:46,815 --> 00:32:48,915
- It's beautiful. - It's lovely.

624
00:32:50,415 --> 00:32:52,084
(Capturing it on her phone)

625
00:32:52,085 --> 00:32:53,985
It looks like a gem.

626
00:32:56,285 --> 00:32:59,055
(How does Yu Ri's hwajeon, as bright as a gem, taste?)

627
00:33:02,055 --> 00:33:04,895
(Closing his eyes)

628
00:33:06,365 --> 00:33:07,395
It's delicious.

629
00:33:09,835 --> 00:33:11,105
(Impressed)

630
00:33:18,945 --> 00:33:19,945
(Nodding)
It's very delicious.

631
00:33:20,946 --> 00:33:21,975
(It's very delicious.)

632
00:33:23,245 --> 00:33:26,885
(The family at the next table tries the hwajeon as well.)

633
00:33:28,185 --> 00:33:31,855
(The dad tries the yellow hwajeon.)

634
00:33:33,025 --> 00:33:35,195
This is a first for me. I like it.

635
00:33:35,895 --> 00:33:36,924
It's the best.

636
00:33:36,925 --> 00:33:39,665
(Crying)

637
00:33:40,535 --> 00:33:43,465
(The other dad is struggling.)

638
00:33:45,065 --> 00:33:47,304
(In the end, he picks up the baby.)

639
00:33:47,305 --> 00:33:49,975
(Small)

640
00:33:50,805 --> 00:33:54,315
(The youngest customer has woken up.)

641
00:33:54,615 --> 00:33:56,885
(Drawing everyone's attention)

642
00:33:57,045 --> 00:33:58,345
- It's a newborn. - Right?

643
00:34:00,155 --> 00:34:01,555
How cute.

644
00:34:07,625 --> 00:34:10,465
(Ultimately moving to the mom's arms)

645
00:34:13,695 --> 00:34:16,435
(Feeling comfortable right away)

646
00:34:17,535 --> 00:34:20,275
(In the meantime, the hwajeon is served.)

647
00:34:20,705 --> 00:34:23,275
(Digging in)

648
00:34:23,975 --> 00:34:27,775
(Enjoying the dessert quickly)

649
00:34:29,515 --> 00:34:32,215
(After finishing the dessert in 50 seconds)

650
00:34:34,615 --> 00:34:38,585
(Taking the baby back so the mom can enjoy her dessert)

651
00:34:38,985 --> 00:34:41,294
(Yawning)

652
00:34:41,295 --> 00:34:43,795
(In the arms of the trusty dad again)

653
00:34:50,665 --> 00:34:51,964
(Current time: 1:20pm)

654
00:34:51,965 --> 00:34:53,535
(It's been 1 hour and 20 minutes since opening.)

655
00:34:54,935 --> 00:34:57,145
- It was great, wasn't it? - Yes.

656
00:34:58,175 --> 00:35:00,244
- Thank you. - Thank you, Chef.

657
00:35:00,245 --> 00:35:02,714
- It was delicious. - Thank you.

658
00:35:02,715 --> 00:35:05,845
- Thank you. - Thank you.

659
00:35:06,415 --> 00:35:09,615
(Another table is done with lunch.)

660
00:35:10,055 --> 00:35:11,224
(Leaving happy)

661
00:35:11,225 --> 00:35:13,595
- Thank you. - Thank you.

662
00:35:14,425 --> 00:35:16,324
Please clean up outside when you have time.

663
00:35:16,325 --> 00:35:17,425
(After the customers have left)

664
00:35:17,565 --> 00:35:20,135
- We have to set the tables up. - I leave it to you.

665
00:35:20,435 --> 00:35:23,405
(Setting the tables up for the next customers)

666
00:35:23,835 --> 00:35:26,935
(Cleaning the tables for Round Two)

667
00:35:27,335 --> 00:35:30,875
(Meanwhile, in the kitchen)

668
00:35:31,945 --> 00:35:35,675
(Chef Paik keeps looking outside the kitchen.)

669
00:35:36,485 --> 00:35:40,715
(Unlike the bright floor, he looks serious.)

670
00:35:41,655 --> 00:35:44,184
(The orders made earlier)

671
00:35:44,185 --> 00:35:46,725
(There are no new orders.)

672
00:35:47,125 --> 00:35:50,694
(No new customers)

673
00:35:50,695 --> 00:35:53,365
Why is our turnover rate so slow?

674
00:35:54,395 --> 00:35:55,935
People usually take a look and come in.

675
00:35:56,235 --> 00:35:57,335
What's going on?

676
00:35:58,535 --> 00:35:59,604
(Thinking)

677
00:35:59,605 --> 00:36:01,574
A lot of people take a look...

678
00:36:01,575 --> 00:36:02,775
but don't come inside.

679
00:36:04,075 --> 00:36:06,914
(Even after looking at the stir-fried spicy chicken,)

680
00:36:06,915 --> 00:36:10,085
(customers walk past.)

681
00:36:14,785 --> 00:36:17,484
(Stopped at the sight of the stir-fried spicy chicken)

682
00:36:17,485 --> 00:36:20,454
(Hesitating)

683
00:36:20,455 --> 00:36:22,124
(They leave.)

684
00:36:22,125 --> 00:36:23,225
Everyone just walks by.

685
00:36:23,825 --> 00:36:25,695
Did everyone already have lunch?

686
00:36:27,035 --> 00:36:30,035
(But it's currently peak time.)

687
00:36:30,605 --> 00:36:32,965
(The storefront is quiet even during peak time.)

688
00:36:33,805 --> 00:36:34,935
What could be the problem?

689
00:36:36,275 --> 00:36:39,075
(Only one thing has changed today.)

690
00:36:39,945 --> 00:36:42,675
(Stir-fried spicy chicken, the main menu)

691
00:36:43,015 --> 00:36:47,655
(Is there a problem with the stir-fried spicy chicken?)

692
00:36:49,215 --> 00:36:53,125
(Something is going wrong.)

693
00:36:53,425 --> 00:36:56,765
(Time keeps ticking.)

694
00:36:57,065 --> 00:37:00,165
(While 30 minutes have passed)

695
00:37:00,865 --> 00:37:02,894
You can sit. Please sit. Thank you.

696
00:37:02,895 --> 00:37:05,235
(Only 1 table with new customers)

697
00:37:05,635 --> 00:37:07,875
We barely had any customers today.

698
00:37:10,375 --> 00:37:12,575
Only two tables were served on the second floor.

699
00:37:12,745 --> 00:37:13,775
This...

700
00:37:14,845 --> 00:37:17,514
(The floor manager is about to report the slow business.)

701
00:37:17,515 --> 00:37:19,315
(Sighing)

702
00:37:24,155 --> 00:37:26,494
We only had two tables on the second floor.

703
00:37:26,495 --> 00:37:27,795
- Today? - Yes.

704
00:37:28,695 --> 00:37:30,764
Other places are packed with customers.

705
00:37:30,765 --> 00:37:31,965
Why not ours?

706
00:37:32,725 --> 00:37:34,494
Because of the nice weather,

707
00:37:34,495 --> 00:37:36,735
we had a pretty decent turnover rate outdoors.

708
00:37:38,935 --> 00:37:40,305
No, our plan failed.

709
00:37:41,775 --> 00:37:42,805
How come?

710
00:37:43,105 --> 00:37:47,945
(The change in the menu plan has failed.)

711
00:37:50,885 --> 00:37:54,885
(What's the issue with the stir-fried spicy chicken?)

712
00:37:55,971 --> 00:38:00,841
(The change in the menu plan has failed.)

713
00:38:03,711 --> 00:38:07,451
(What's the issue with the stir-fried spicy chicken?)

714
00:38:08,121 --> 00:38:11,791
(Chef Paik looks at the leftover stir-fried spicy chicken.)

715
00:38:30,241 --> 00:38:32,340
(Looking at the stir-fried spicy chicken...)

716
00:38:32,341 --> 00:38:35,781
(through the big window from a customer's perspective)

717
00:38:37,911 --> 00:38:40,180
(Checking the stir-fried spicy chicken...)

718
00:38:40,181 --> 00:38:42,121
(on the customer's table)

719
00:38:42,651 --> 00:38:46,651
(Did Chef Paik find a solution?)

720
00:38:47,461 --> 00:38:49,121
Let's change our plan.

721
00:38:49,221 --> 00:38:50,260
Sorry?

722
00:38:50,261 --> 00:38:53,331
(Change our plan?)

723
00:38:54,501 --> 00:38:56,361
The food on the customer's table looks spicy.

724
00:38:57,701 --> 00:38:58,931
The one they're eating, right?

725
00:38:59,501 --> 00:39:03,001
In short, it's the timing.

726
00:39:04,071 --> 00:39:06,471
Customers stopped for a minute...

727
00:39:07,141 --> 00:39:09,381
- when the food was served outside. - Right.

728
00:39:10,451 --> 00:39:13,421
But once the food was served, we had fewer customers.

729
00:39:13,921 --> 00:39:15,050
True.

730
00:39:15,051 --> 00:39:16,451
Contrary to today,

731
00:39:16,891 --> 00:39:18,920
customers flooded in...

732
00:39:18,921 --> 00:39:21,121
when the food was served outside yesterday.

733
00:39:22,791 --> 00:39:25,431
(Yesterday's menu was a pan of pork belly.)

734
00:39:25,991 --> 00:39:28,831
(A taste everyone enjoys)

735
00:39:30,171 --> 00:39:33,331
(An easy-to-understand grilled meat dish)

736
00:39:33,541 --> 00:39:36,501
(Thanks to it, the pan of pork belly...)

737
00:39:36,601 --> 00:39:38,410
(Looking)

738
00:39:38,411 --> 00:39:39,571
That looks good.

739
00:39:40,611 --> 00:39:43,611
(worked as a billboard to attract customers.)

740
00:39:44,151 --> 00:39:46,821
(But today's stir-fried spicy chicken...)

741
00:39:48,321 --> 00:39:51,791
(is red, which is unfamiliar.)

742
00:39:51,951 --> 00:39:53,421
- They think it'll be spicy. - I see.

743
00:39:53,561 --> 00:39:54,821
What's more, it's Korean food.

744
00:39:55,821 --> 00:39:58,630
- So people fear the color red. - Yes.

745
00:39:58,631 --> 00:39:59,690
They're scared.

746
00:39:59,691 --> 00:40:01,260
It's totally different.

747
00:40:01,261 --> 00:40:03,160
To us, it looks appetizing.

748
00:40:03,161 --> 00:40:04,171
Exactly.

749
00:40:04,901 --> 00:40:08,171
(They can't give up like this.)

750
00:40:08,601 --> 00:40:09,901
Give me the menu.

751
00:40:13,371 --> 00:40:14,441
It's scary.

752
00:40:15,611 --> 00:40:17,180
Now that I look at it, it's scary.

753
00:40:17,181 --> 00:40:19,451
(The photo on the menu is red.)

754
00:40:20,721 --> 00:40:22,080
We just need to take another one. Hold on.

755
00:40:22,081 --> 00:40:23,081
Got it.

756
00:40:23,621 --> 00:40:25,051
Let's make another menu.

757
00:40:25,391 --> 00:40:27,360
- Menu? - The other one... Look here.

758
00:40:27,361 --> 00:40:29,161
(Adding another menu?)

759
00:40:29,661 --> 00:40:32,190
Please add another page.

760
00:40:32,191 --> 00:40:34,231
- The first page will be soy sauce, - Yes?

761
00:40:34,301 --> 00:40:35,301
and the next page...

762
00:40:35,302 --> 00:40:36,731
- will be the current menu. - Okay.

763
00:40:36,931 --> 00:40:39,501
Give them a choice of spicy and non-spicy.

764
00:40:39,601 --> 00:40:40,771
- Understood. - Okay.

765
00:40:42,671 --> 00:40:44,911
(If they lost customers because it looks spicy,)

766
00:40:45,871 --> 00:40:49,041
(attract them with a non-spicy menu!)

767
00:40:50,281 --> 00:40:54,351
(Stir-fried soy sauce chicken, the strategy to draw in customers)

768
00:40:54,821 --> 00:40:57,591
(Starting on the soy sauce chicken)

769
00:40:58,151 --> 00:41:00,521
(Filling the new hotel pan with onions)

770
00:41:02,161 --> 00:41:04,291
(After adding all sorts of condiments)

771
00:41:05,291 --> 00:41:07,031
(And here is...)

772
00:41:07,661 --> 00:41:11,601
(the core of the sauce, soy sauce.)

773
00:41:12,071 --> 00:41:15,171
(Boiling it down as is in the induction-safe hotel pan)

774
00:41:17,041 --> 00:41:21,411
(The chicken is being boiled down in the soy sauce.)

775
00:41:23,111 --> 00:41:26,011
(Boosting the sweet and savory flavors)

776
00:41:26,481 --> 00:41:30,591
(After adding in dark soy sauce)

777
00:41:31,091 --> 00:41:32,420
- Place them inside. - Okay.

778
00:41:32,421 --> 00:41:35,221
(Finishing them off in the oven)

779
00:41:37,531 --> 00:41:41,461
(The soy sauce chicken is in the oven.)

780
00:41:42,701 --> 00:41:46,101
(What will it look like in 2 hours?)

781
00:41:47,201 --> 00:41:50,971
(Time passes toward dinner.)

782
00:41:52,211 --> 00:41:55,611
(Before they know it, it's evening in Lyon.)

783
00:41:55,641 --> 00:41:57,650
(Single Pan House)

784
00:41:57,651 --> 00:42:01,481
(Preparing for their first-ever dinner business)

785
00:42:02,421 --> 00:42:04,090
- I'm back. - Hi.

786
00:42:04,091 --> 00:42:05,191
- Hi. - Hey.

787
00:42:06,491 --> 00:42:12,691
(On Friday night, Rue Merciere...)

788
00:42:13,131 --> 00:42:15,761
(is already packed with people.)

789
00:42:16,201 --> 00:42:19,271
(It's starting to get crowded as expected on a Friday night.)

790
00:42:19,871 --> 00:42:23,611
(If only we could attract all those customers...)

791
00:42:24,311 --> 00:42:27,981
(The success depends on...)

792
00:42:29,881 --> 00:42:31,280
(Anxious)

793
00:42:31,281 --> 00:42:34,581
(the stir-fried soy sauce chicken inside the oven.)

794
00:42:36,181 --> 00:42:37,620
(Did the soy sauce chicken cook well?)

795
00:42:37,621 --> 00:42:39,591
Are the chicken legs cooking well?

796
00:42:39,651 --> 00:42:40,961
- The new batch. - Yes.

797
00:42:47,161 --> 00:42:49,061
The chicken looks amazing.

798
00:42:49,401 --> 00:42:53,101
(Here comes the juicy-looking soy sauce chicken.)

799
00:42:53,501 --> 00:42:55,101
- The color looks fine. - Right?

800
00:42:57,571 --> 00:42:59,540
Passing by. Please make way.

801
00:42:59,541 --> 00:43:00,980
(Stir-fried soy sauce chicken,)

802
00:43:00,981 --> 00:43:02,480
(the textbook example of sweet and savory,)

803
00:43:02,481 --> 00:43:04,011
(makes its way out.)

804
00:43:04,851 --> 00:43:10,121
(Placing it in front of the big window)

805
00:43:10,621 --> 00:43:16,191
(Catching people's attention as soon as it appeared)

806
00:43:17,391 --> 00:43:18,891
