1076
00:56:30,781 --> 00:56:31,851
It's not spicy.

1077
00:56:32,851 --> 00:56:34,961
It's not spicy at all. It's sweet.

1078
00:56:37,091 --> 00:56:38,660
It's not bad.

1079
00:56:38,661 --> 00:56:41,601
I'm glad we can enjoy it comfortably.

1080
00:56:43,301 --> 00:56:48,141
(While the first customers for soy sauce flavor enjoy their meal)

1081
00:56:53,941 --> 00:56:57,011
(Showing interest in the big window)

1082
00:56:58,011 --> 00:57:00,651
(Showing interest in the stand sign)

1083
00:57:05,021 --> 00:57:08,290
(Spotting stir-fried soy sauce chicken on the table)

1084
00:57:08,291 --> 00:57:09,361
Hello.

1085
00:57:09,991 --> 00:57:13,431
(They stare at the chicken for a long time.)

1086
00:57:15,101 --> 00:57:16,900
- Could we have a meal? - Yes.

1087
00:57:16,901 --> 00:57:18,470
Two people? Okay.

1088
00:57:18,471 --> 00:57:19,971
(After pondering,)

1089
00:57:20,501 --> 00:57:24,141
(they sit at an outdoor table.)

1090
00:57:24,441 --> 00:57:25,870
Here's the menu.

1091
00:57:25,871 --> 00:57:26,971
Thank you.

1092
00:57:29,111 --> 00:57:30,241
They have two flavors.

1093
00:57:33,581 --> 00:57:36,851
(They're curious about the menu the adjacent table is having.)

1094
00:57:37,551 --> 00:57:39,851
(Even as they're seated, they keep glancing over.)

1095
00:57:40,491 --> 00:57:42,461
(Thinking)

1096
00:57:42,821 --> 00:57:45,861
(At that moment, another group of customers appear.)

1097
00:57:46,531 --> 00:57:48,531
- Hello. - Hello.

1098
00:57:49,001 --> 00:57:51,530
It's a new Korean restaurant.

1099
00:57:51,531 --> 00:57:53,271
- Shall we give it a go? - Would you like to?

1100
00:57:53,871 --> 00:57:54,871
Okay.

1101
00:57:55,771 --> 00:57:59,341
(They choose to sit outdoors.)

1102
00:57:59,941 --> 00:58:01,741
(Staring)

1103
00:58:01,911 --> 00:58:03,841
- Are you fine with that? - Yes, it looks okay.

1104
00:58:05,151 --> 00:58:08,081
(After a glance at the next table, they choose soy sauce flavor.)

1105
00:58:09,151 --> 00:58:11,621
(And the two customers who couldn't decide...)

1106
00:58:12,091 --> 00:58:14,021
- Do you want the non-spicy one? - Yes.

1107
00:58:15,391 --> 00:58:18,331
(They order soy sauce flavor too.)

1108
00:58:18,791 --> 00:58:20,160
(The orders for stir-fried soy sauce chicken come in.)

1109
00:58:20,161 --> 00:58:21,401
They're both non-spicy chicken.

1110
00:58:32,671 --> 00:58:34,271
You're more famous than BTS.

1111
00:58:35,581 --> 00:58:36,641
Table 13.

1112
00:58:41,521 --> 00:58:42,581
(1 stir-fried soy sauce chicken served)

1113
00:58:43,681 --> 00:58:46,091
(Attracting attention)

1114
00:58:46,851 --> 00:58:47,851
(1 stir-fried soy sauce chicken served)

1115
00:58:49,591 --> 00:58:54,230
(2 soy sauce flavors each)

1116
00:58:54,231 --> 00:58:57,331
(All the outdoor tables are occupied with soy sauce flavor.)

1117
00:58:57,501 --> 00:59:01,741
The chicken tastes good with the sauce.

1118
00:59:02,071 --> 00:59:04,641
Wait for the cheese to melt, then have them together.

1119
00:59:04,811 --> 00:59:06,470
- Enjoy your meal. - Thank you.

1120
00:59:06,471 --> 00:59:07,741
(John leaves after sharing how to eat the dish.)

1121
00:59:08,541 --> 00:59:11,711
(Taking the first bite of stir-fried soy sauce chicken)

1122
00:59:12,751 --> 00:59:13,781
(Surprised)

1123
00:59:14,751 --> 00:59:18,021
(Nodding)

1124
00:59:19,021 --> 00:59:22,361
(Stir-fried soy sauce chicken placed outdoors...)

1125
00:59:24,021 --> 00:59:27,560
(attracts passersby's attention.)

1126
00:59:27,561 --> 00:59:30,701
(Turning around)

1127
00:59:31,201 --> 00:59:33,931
(Glancing)

1128
00:59:34,271 --> 00:59:35,940
- Welcome. - This way.

1129
00:59:35,941 --> 00:59:37,040
(4 more customers)

1130
00:59:37,041 --> 00:59:38,311
Welcome.

1131
00:59:39,171 --> 00:59:40,271
Welcome.

1132
00:59:41,911 --> 00:59:44,481
(2 more customers)

1133
00:59:44,541 --> 00:59:45,580
Welcome.

1134
00:59:45,581 --> 00:59:46,681
(2 more customers)

1135
00:59:47,351 --> 00:59:51,721
(Customers come in nonstop!)

1136
00:59:52,291 --> 00:59:54,451
- Hello. - Do you have a table for two?

1137
00:59:54,661 --> 00:59:58,130
Well, no. Every table is full right now.

1138
00:59:58,131 --> 01:00:03,001
- Okay. - Maybe 20 to 30 minutes wait.

1139
01:00:04,531 --> 01:00:07,001
(Current time: 8pm, only 1 hour since they started)

1140
01:00:07,531 --> 01:00:10,441
(Single Pan House is full.)

1141
01:00:10,841 --> 01:00:13,641
(During lunch, the 2nd floor only had 2 groups of customers.)

1142
01:00:14,341 --> 01:00:17,511
(It's become a full house for dinner!)

1143
01:00:17,881 --> 01:00:19,751
(Stir-fried spicy chicken)

1144
01:00:20,381 --> 01:00:22,521
(All they did was add the soy sauce flavor option.)

1145
01:00:23,021 --> 01:00:25,321
- We got a lot of orders. - What?

1146
01:00:25,791 --> 01:00:27,391
We have a lot.

1147
01:00:27,891 --> 01:00:30,391
(They're racking in sales now.)

1148
01:00:31,431 --> 01:00:32,660
(How much sales did they make so far?)

1149
01:00:32,661 --> 01:00:33,731
What?

1150
01:00:35,031 --> 01:00:36,200
(62 euros, 95 euros, 90 euros)

1151
01:00:36,201 --> 01:00:37,900
(247 euros)

1152
01:00:37,901 --> 01:00:40,130
(80 euros, 144 euros, 90 euros, 91 euros, 79 euros, 92 euros)

1153
01:00:40,131 --> 01:00:42,471
(566 euros)

1154
01:00:42,841 --> 01:00:44,370
(82 euros, 92 euros, 79 euros, 79 euros)

1155
01:00:44,371 --> 01:00:47,011
(332 euros)

1156
01:00:47,441 --> 01:00:48,910
(Current dinner sales)

1157
01:00:48,911 --> 01:00:52,951
(1,105 euros, which is about 1,800 dollars)

1158
01:00:53,581 --> 01:00:57,581
(They broke their highest sales record in just 1 hour!)

1159
01:00:58,321 --> 01:00:59,450
(A business that flopped...)

1160
01:00:59,451 --> 01:01:03,591
(became a huge success!)

1161
01:01:04,661 --> 01:01:05,690
(But the abundance of customers means...)

1162
01:01:05,691 --> 01:01:06,861
How's everything upstairs?

1163
01:01:09,101 --> 01:01:10,700
- Are you okay? - Yes.

1164
01:01:10,701 --> 01:01:12,530
Things have slowed down here,

1165
01:01:12,531 --> 01:01:14,231
so the food should be served fast. Everything else is fine.

1166
01:01:14,701 --> 01:01:17,601
(Returning to the 1st floor)

1167
01:01:18,911 --> 01:01:20,511
- Table 9. - Table 9.

1168
01:01:20,811 --> 01:01:22,911
(Going back upstairs)

1169
01:01:23,881 --> 01:01:26,611
(Coming down again)

1170
01:01:27,911 --> 01:01:32,691
(The floor manager walks up and down the stairs nonstop.)

1171
01:01:34,351 --> 01:01:38,431
(Once he's done with the 2nd floor, he checks the outdoor tables.)

1172
01:01:38,591 --> 01:01:42,331
We need to serve them rice balls.

1173
01:01:42,901 --> 01:01:44,801
It's so busy.

1174
01:01:46,631 --> 01:01:49,571
(He's making rice balls.)

1175
01:01:53,841 --> 01:01:55,211
We got new orders.

1176
01:01:56,841 --> 01:01:58,780
Two for Table Fifteen.

1177
01:01:58,781 --> 01:02:01,581
You didn't write whether it's spicy or not for Table 15.

1178
01:02:02,781 --> 01:02:04,320
Is it spicy or non-spicy for Table 15?

1179
01:02:04,321 --> 01:02:06,151
(The order doesn't specify the flavor.)

1180
01:02:07,651 --> 01:02:09,491
(He can't hear him.)

1181
01:02:09,721 --> 01:02:13,690
Yu Ri, can you make one lemon soju?

1182
01:02:13,691 --> 01:02:16,231
It's here. I've already made it.

1183
01:02:16,501 --> 01:02:17,831
- I just need to pour it out? - Yes.

1184
01:02:18,501 --> 01:02:19,570
It's so hectic.

1185
01:02:19,571 --> 01:02:20,601
(He forgot because things are hectic.)

1186
01:02:20,771 --> 01:02:22,840
You should start making coffee now.

1187
01:02:22,841 --> 01:02:24,441
- Okay. - What about this?

1188
01:02:26,211 --> 01:02:27,711
Where's the blender?

1189
01:02:27,811 --> 01:02:29,040
- Where is it? - Table Six.

1190
01:02:29,041 --> 01:02:30,211
- The coffee blender. - Table Six.

1191
01:02:30,611 --> 01:02:32,381
- Table Six. - In the freezer.

1192
01:02:32,481 --> 01:02:33,511
In the freezer?

1193
01:02:35,451 --> 01:02:37,051
You're all over the place for sure.

1194
01:02:39,151 --> 01:02:40,290
(To the point he forgot what he was doing)

1195
01:02:40,291 --> 01:02:41,591
I'm all over the place.

1196
01:02:42,921 --> 01:02:45,861
Is it spicy or not for Table 15?

1197
01:02:46,961 --> 01:02:48,961
What? Table 15?

1198
01:02:49,961 --> 01:02:51,101
I also don't know.

1199
01:02:51,671 --> 01:02:53,801
(In the end, his brain stops functioning.)

1200
01:02:53,971 --> 01:02:56,671
John, your mind is elsewhere.

1201
01:02:57,971 --> 01:03:00,910
Table 15 is non-spicy. Sorry.

1202
01:03:00,911 --> 01:03:02,511
(Soy sauce flavor)

1203
01:03:03,281 --> 01:03:04,980
(He got a hold of himself pretty fast.)

1204
01:03:04,981 --> 01:03:06,710
- I forgot to write it. - I'll do it.

1205
01:03:06,711 --> 01:03:07,711
Okay.

1206
01:03:08,011 --> 01:03:09,221
Take it slow.

1207
01:03:10,721 --> 01:03:12,591
I can't take it slow.

1208
01:03:14,821 --> 01:03:15,920
Four servings.

1209
01:03:15,921 --> 01:03:19,731
(The new order is 4 servings of soy sauce flavor.)

1210
01:03:20,761 --> 01:03:23,161
(A big pan of soy sauce flavor for 4 people)

1211
01:03:25,871 --> 01:03:27,570
(Cheered on by a stranger)

1212
01:03:27,571 --> 01:03:28,641
Table Six.

1213
01:03:28,801 --> 01:03:31,201
(Making a huge pan of stir-fried soy sauce chicken)

1214
01:03:32,511 --> 01:03:35,411
(The pan is filled up generously.)

1215
01:03:36,341 --> 01:03:38,981
(Completed with heaps of cheese)

1216
01:03:40,011 --> 01:03:41,081
Passing by.

1217
01:03:42,051 --> 01:03:43,120
- Table Six. - My gosh.

1218
01:03:43,121 --> 01:03:44,481
- It's heavy. - It's okay.

1219
01:03:45,321 --> 01:03:46,821
Can you help me with the fire?

1220
01:03:47,551 --> 01:03:48,591
Okay.

1221
01:03:50,021 --> 01:03:52,130
(A generous portion of the pan for 4)

1222
01:03:52,131 --> 01:03:54,191
(Delivered quickly)

1223
01:03:57,301 --> 01:04:00,501
(The size of the pan attracts their attention.)

1224
01:04:01,031 --> 01:04:03,171
(Shocked)

1225
01:04:03,701 --> 01:04:05,040
- That's kind of big. - The chicken...

1226
01:04:05,041 --> 01:04:06,211
It's quite big, though.

1227
01:04:07,741 --> 01:04:10,241
Daddy, I'm counting on you to help me finish this.

1228
01:04:10,811 --> 01:04:12,311
I thought that was only for me.

1229
01:04:13,811 --> 01:04:15,051
Are you sure you can?

1230
01:04:16,521 --> 01:04:19,121
(I'm joking.)

1231
01:04:19,421 --> 01:04:21,091
- Here? - Thank you.

1232
01:04:22,191 --> 01:04:24,391
- I'll take some later. - Here.

1233
01:04:24,961 --> 01:04:27,460
(He gives the food to his family first.)

1234
01:04:27,461 --> 01:04:28,831
The chicken is very tender.

1235
01:04:30,531 --> 01:04:32,370
It's actually better than I thought.

1236
01:04:32,371 --> 01:04:33,371
Yes?

1237
01:04:33,971 --> 01:04:38,471
(The dad is busy giving out the food that he hasn't had a single bite.)

1238
01:04:38,911 --> 01:04:39,941
Me.

1239
01:04:40,141 --> 01:04:42,741
(A pile of potatoes)

1240
01:04:43,581 --> 01:04:44,911
Why won't you give him chicken?

1241
01:04:46,211 --> 01:04:50,181
(Giving him only potatoes and rice cakes)

1242
01:04:50,981 --> 01:04:54,191
(He distributes chicken fairly too.)

1243
01:04:54,451 --> 01:04:55,590
Do you like it?

1244
01:04:55,591 --> 01:04:57,320
(Answering with his eyebrows)

1245
01:04:57,321 --> 01:04:59,161
It's not that I like it. I love it.

1246
01:04:59,961 --> 01:05:02,161
Yes, very nice.

1247
01:05:03,131 --> 01:05:05,901
(Si Yoon notes that they're almost done with the food.)

1248
01:05:06,871 --> 01:05:07,900
They... What's that again?

1249
01:05:07,901 --> 01:05:09,700
- That table. - You make fried rice.

1250
01:05:09,701 --> 01:05:11,370
I'll focus on cleaning the table.

1251
01:05:11,371 --> 01:05:13,811
- Fried rice? - Let's do that. Oh, right.

1252
01:05:14,471 --> 01:05:17,280
(There's no fried rice today.)

1253
01:05:17,281 --> 01:05:18,511
- I'll do it later. - Rice balls, you mean?

1254
01:05:18,681 --> 01:05:20,581
- Yes. I'll do it later. - Okay.

1255
01:05:21,611 --> 01:05:23,551
One serving of rice ball.

1256
01:05:26,521 --> 01:05:29,261
(Scooping up a lot since it's for 4 people)

1257
01:05:29,821 --> 01:05:32,261
(Adding sesame oil onto the rice ball)

1258
01:05:32,661 --> 01:05:35,231
(Squeezing out savory mayonnaise)

1259
01:05:40,131 --> 01:05:42,141
(Feeling unnecessarily nervous)

1260
01:05:42,871 --> 01:05:43,901
Okay.

1261
01:05:45,411 --> 01:05:48,011
(After glancing at them...)

1262
01:05:48,311 --> 01:05:49,611
- One for you. - Okay, thank you.

1263
01:05:50,081 --> 01:05:51,850
- One for you. - Thank you.

1264
01:05:51,851 --> 01:05:52,880
Okay.

1265
01:05:52,881 --> 01:05:54,681
This is called rice balls.

1266
01:05:55,881 --> 01:05:57,921
(Demonstrating how to make rice balls)

1267
01:05:58,421 --> 01:06:01,821
(The kids are very interested.)

1268
01:06:02,191 --> 01:06:03,290
Do you want to do it?

1269
01:06:03,291 --> 01:06:04,391
Come here.

1270
01:06:05,731 --> 01:06:06,891
Make a little...

1271
01:06:07,791 --> 01:06:08,861
ball.

1272
01:06:09,161 --> 01:06:11,831
My mom used to make this for me.

1273
01:06:12,831 --> 01:06:15,401
You can practice it with my playdough.

1274
01:06:15,901 --> 01:06:19,071
(Telling her mom to practice with her toy)

1275
01:06:19,541 --> 01:06:20,640
Okay, thank you.

1276
01:06:20,641 --> 01:06:21,671
Thank you.

1277
01:06:22,011 --> 01:06:25,881
(Making rice balls with her small hand)

1278
01:06:26,051 --> 01:06:27,580
I'll do it with two hands.

1279
01:06:27,581 --> 01:06:29,520
No, use one hand.

1280
01:06:29,521 --> 01:06:31,121
(The brother gives up his glove for her.)

1281
01:06:33,321 --> 01:06:35,021
I'll do it small.

1282
01:06:35,321 --> 01:06:38,831
(The first rice ball goes on Mom's plate.)

1283
01:06:42,731 --> 01:06:44,801
(Humming)

1284
01:06:45,701 --> 01:06:47,331
This is a nice ball, right?

1285
01:06:47,901 --> 01:06:50,141
(Round)

1286
01:06:50,571 --> 01:06:52,641
(The pretty one is mine.)

1287
01:06:53,071 --> 01:06:54,311
That was for you.

1288
01:06:54,641 --> 01:06:56,911
(The well-made rice ball goes on my plate.)

1289
01:06:57,381 --> 01:06:59,611
(Making rice balls with much effort)

1290
01:07:00,111 --> 01:07:02,021
This is very nice.

1291
01:07:02,221 --> 01:07:05,721
(They finish their meal happily with rice balls.)

1292
01:07:06,121 --> 01:07:09,421
(Meanwhile, the customers come downstairs after their meal.)

1293
01:07:09,621 --> 01:07:11,761
(Greeting someone enthusiastically.)

1294
01:07:12,631 --> 01:07:15,861
(The customers on the 1st floor respond.)

1295
01:07:16,101 --> 01:07:17,231
How's your meal?

1296
01:07:17,401 --> 01:07:18,770
It's very nice.

1297
01:07:18,771 --> 01:07:19,801
Good.

1298
01:07:20,031 --> 01:07:21,301
Do you know each other?

1299
01:07:21,801 --> 01:07:24,200
We were just queuing outside together.

1300
01:07:24,201 --> 01:07:25,271
(Her waiting friend)

1301
01:07:26,411 --> 01:07:27,871
So you had...

1302
01:07:28,641 --> 01:07:31,180
three beers and the menu for two people.

1303
01:07:31,181 --> 01:07:32,981
- Yes. - That's it.

1304
01:07:34,811 --> 01:07:36,220
I should've drunk soju.

1305
01:07:36,221 --> 01:07:37,981
(It's a shame he didn't.)

1306
01:07:38,421 --> 01:07:39,450
(He puts soju behind and pays for his meal.)

1307
01:07:39,451 --> 01:07:40,621
You're welcome.

1308
01:07:42,321 --> 01:07:43,921
Did you have some drink?

1309
01:07:44,861 --> 01:07:46,030
- Drink? - Yes.

1310
01:07:46,031 --> 01:07:47,031
(Tempted)

1311
01:07:47,161 --> 01:07:48,501
Listen to her.

1312
01:07:48,961 --> 01:07:50,800
(Reaching for his wife hurriedly)

1313
01:07:50,801 --> 01:07:52,800
I'm just wondering if you had some drink.

1314
01:07:52,801 --> 01:07:54,471
- No. - Do you guys want a drink?

1315
01:07:54,871 --> 01:07:56,271
(Grabbing his arm urgently)

1316
01:07:56,471 --> 01:07:59,041
- You can join us if you want. - No, thank you.

1317
01:07:59,171 --> 01:08:00,840
If you want to join us, it's fine.

1318
01:08:00,841 --> 01:08:03,541
We have some more.

1319
01:08:04,141 --> 01:08:06,380
- No. - I mean, you can have some water.

1320
01:08:06,381 --> 01:08:08,151
And you can have some makgeolli.

1321
01:08:08,921 --> 01:08:10,151
He's getting old.

1322
01:08:10,481 --> 01:08:12,250
- He's getting old. - No, we're also getting old.

1323
01:08:12,251 --> 01:08:14,051
Baby, do you want to move up?

1324
01:08:14,221 --> 01:08:15,560
I think she wants to go home.

1325
01:08:15,561 --> 01:08:16,761
I know, but I mean...

1326
01:08:18,661 --> 01:08:21,260
(She goes on a strike.)

1327
01:08:21,261 --> 01:08:23,561
(The child-at-heart wants to spend more time here.)

1328
01:08:23,931 --> 01:08:25,771
- You can have some tap water. - Just five minutes.

1329
01:08:26,171 --> 01:08:28,071
Five minutes.

1330
01:08:28,541 --> 01:08:30,601
Five minutes. Okay, you're allowed.

1331
01:08:31,141 --> 01:08:32,710
- All right. - No.

1332
01:08:32,711 --> 01:08:33,870
(The waiting buddy meeting starts with much difficulty.)

1333
01:08:33,871 --> 01:08:34,911
Stop it.

1334
01:08:34,971 --> 01:08:36,380
- Cheers. - Cheers.

1335
01:08:36,381 --> 01:08:39,111
(That's how 5 minutes turned into 50 minutes.)

1336
01:08:39,711 --> 01:08:42,651
(Current time: 8:30pm, it's been 1.5 hours since opening.)

1337
01:08:43,281 --> 01:08:45,951
(The sun has set completely.)

1338
01:08:47,791 --> 01:08:49,991
(The night on Rue Merciere lights up.)

1339
01:08:50,521 --> 01:08:53,631
(It now has the highest volume of foot traffic.)

1340
01:08:57,931 --> 01:09:02,571
(Friday night's peak time is here.)

1341
01:09:03,641 --> 01:09:06,871
(Other restaurants are cashing in on it big time.)

1342
01:09:07,471 --> 01:09:10,341
(Single Pan House, which shines the brightest)

1343
01:09:11,681 --> 01:09:14,511
(Once customers are done with their meals,)

1344
01:09:14,811 --> 01:09:17,381
(next customers fill up the seats.)

1345
01:09:17,821 --> 01:09:20,591
(There are table turnovers!)

1346
01:09:25,021 --> 01:09:26,091
Please come in.

1347
01:09:27,631 --> 01:09:28,700
- They're going upstairs. - Four people?

1348
01:09:28,701 --> 01:09:29,701
- Four? - Four, yes.

1349
01:09:30,231 --> 01:09:32,371
(As soon as the table is cleared,)

1350
01:09:33,371 --> 01:09:34,830
(it's soon filled with new people.)

1351
01:09:34,831 --> 01:09:36,240
(They're new customers too.)

1352
01:09:36,241 --> 01:09:39,241
(It's soon filled with new people.)

1353
01:09:40,011 --> 01:09:43,641
(The new customers share something in common.)

1354
01:09:43,741 --> 01:09:44,780
Choice.

1355
01:09:44,781 --> 01:09:46,380
(When choosing between spicy and soy sauce flavors...)

1356
01:09:46,381 --> 01:09:48,381
You choose. It's your birthday.

1357
01:09:48,981 --> 01:09:53,251
(She chooses soy sauce flavor.)

1358
01:09:53,721 --> 01:09:56,420
(Another group of new customers)

1359
01:09:56,421 --> 01:09:59,131
We'd like soy sauce flavor.

1360
01:10:00,231 --> 01:10:02,431
(Choosing soy sauce flavor without hesitation)

1361
01:10:03,361 --> 01:10:04,701
If you don't mind, can we order the non-spicy one?

1362
01:10:07,001 --> 01:10:09,000
I don't like spicy food.

1363
01:10:09,001 --> 01:10:10,141
Okay, let's order non-spicy.

1364
01:10:11,071 --> 01:10:14,211
(They choose soy sauce flavor.)

1365
01:10:14,841 --> 01:10:16,011
Not spicy.

1366
01:10:16,381 --> 01:10:18,010
Non-spicy?

1367
01:10:18,011 --> 01:10:19,081
Spicy for me.

1368
01:10:20,351 --> 01:10:22,020
(2 soy sauce, 2 soy sauce, 2 soy sauce,)

1369
01:10:22,021 --> 01:10:23,581
(2 spicy, 4 soy sauce, 2 soy sauce)

1370
01:10:24,121 --> 01:10:26,751
(It could be due to the outdoor soy sauce flavor strategy.)

1371
01:10:27,321 --> 01:10:28,590
- We got new orders. - Okay.

1372
01:10:28,591 --> 01:10:29,821
(They got many orders of stir-fried soy sauce chicken.)

1373
01:10:30,221 --> 01:10:34,660
(Orders keep coming in.)

1374
01:10:34,661 --> 01:10:36,061
The two-people pan...

1375
01:10:38,161 --> 01:10:39,600
We only have three pans left.

1376
01:10:39,601 --> 01:10:41,331
(We only have 3 pans left!)

1377
01:10:41,601 --> 01:10:44,371
(They've almost run out of pans.)

1378
01:10:44,701 --> 01:10:47,340
We need to clean the pans.

1379
01:10:47,341 --> 01:10:48,441
(The kitchen is on the verge of stopping altogether.)

1380
01:10:48,511 --> 01:10:50,210
(At that moment)

1381
01:10:50,211 --> 01:10:52,410
Here are two clean pans.

1382
01:10:52,411 --> 01:10:53,610
- Thank you. - No problem.

1383
01:10:53,611 --> 01:10:55,350
(The pans are refilled?)

1384
01:10:55,351 --> 01:10:57,081
(Rushing)

1385
01:10:59,391 --> 01:11:00,391
(Amazed)

1386
01:11:01,421 --> 01:11:02,821
He does all the dishes on his own.

1387
01:11:03,891 --> 01:11:06,091
(He was busy cleaning the hall.)

1388
01:11:07,491 --> 01:11:09,960
(Shocked)

1389
01:11:09,961 --> 01:11:10,961
Let's see.

1390
01:11:10,962 --> 01:11:12,701
(He spots the dishes piled up.)

1391
01:11:12,831 --> 01:11:13,901
I should wash them quickly.

1392
01:11:14,301 --> 01:11:15,941
I need to do it fast to take in customers faster.

1393
01:11:17,501 --> 01:11:20,871
(Scrubbing)

1394
01:11:21,771 --> 01:11:24,541
(He washes the pans first and passes them to the chefs.)

1395
01:11:24,881 --> 01:11:27,451
(Washing the plates with water)

1396
01:11:31,121 --> 01:11:33,290
(Once Si Yoon passes by a place,)

1397
01:11:33,291 --> 01:11:36,321
(it becomes very clean.)

1398
01:11:36,791 --> 01:11:37,791
(Dashing)

1399
01:11:37,792 --> 01:11:41,631
(He refills the plates after he refills the pans.)

1400
01:11:42,331 --> 01:11:44,600
Si Yoon has good stamina, so he can run around.

1401
01:11:44,601 --> 01:11:45,601
- It's nice. - He...

1402
01:11:46,371 --> 01:11:47,930
I should put this in the kitchen.

1403
01:11:47,931 --> 01:11:49,771
- Thank you. - It's nothing.

1404
01:11:50,701 --> 01:11:51,841
Good job, Si Yoon.

1405
01:11:52,971 --> 01:11:54,111
He's so reliable.

1406
01:11:56,481 --> 01:11:58,640
Where did the tongs and scissors go?

1407
01:11:58,641 --> 01:12:00,951
- Here. No, they're not it. - Where?

1408
01:12:02,011 --> 01:12:03,520
(The tongs and scissors that were just here are gone.)

1409
01:12:03,521 --> 01:12:05,351
Did you take the tongs and scissors in the jar?

1410
01:12:06,121 --> 01:12:07,721
- They were here. - Yes.

1411
01:12:07,751 --> 01:12:10,691
(He washed them.)

1412
01:12:10,861 --> 01:12:12,791
Why did you take them? It's a problem...

1413
01:12:12,861 --> 01:12:14,130
that you clean up so fast, but it's good.

1414
01:12:14,131 --> 01:12:16,860
- It's perfect. - I won't clean the ones up here.

1415
01:12:16,861 --> 01:12:18,561
- Perfect. Good job. - Because you use them.

1416
01:12:19,831 --> 01:12:22,541
(Thanks to Si Yoon who cleans them all,)

1417
01:12:23,371 --> 01:12:26,740
(the kitchen is moving faster.)

1418
01:12:26,741 --> 01:12:27,941
We'll serve Table Five.

1419
01:12:28,671 --> 01:12:30,110
Table 15 should be served too.

1420
01:12:30,111 --> 01:12:31,441
Okay. I'm getting ready for it.

1421
01:12:42,961 --> 01:12:47,130
(The dishes are completed without a problem.)

1422
01:12:47,131 --> 01:12:48,231
Table 15.

1423
01:13:01,041 --> 01:13:04,081
(Tasting the stretchy cheese)

1424
01:13:07,151 --> 01:13:10,881
(Enjoying the rice balls too)

1425
01:13:13,221 --> 01:13:16,391
(The four-person table starts to make the rice balls too.)

1426
01:13:16,521 --> 01:13:19,231
(Holding tightly)

1427
01:13:19,491 --> 01:13:21,191
Do you like my rice balls?

1428
01:13:21,691 --> 01:13:23,501
They're a bit problematic.

1429
01:13:23,831 --> 01:13:26,471
(They're flat for some reason.)

1430
01:13:26,671 --> 01:13:29,771
Do Koreans make them by hand? Impressive.

1431
01:13:30,671 --> 01:13:32,510
Yes, but with one hand...

1432
01:13:32,511 --> 01:13:33,811
It's not easy using one hand.

1433
01:13:34,971 --> 01:13:37,910
Look. This one turned out really well.

1434
01:13:37,911 --> 01:13:39,280
- Look. - It's really pretty.

1435
01:13:39,281 --> 01:13:40,350
(Please look at it.)

1436
01:13:40,351 --> 01:13:41,851
(Nodding)

1437
01:13:42,051 --> 01:13:43,851
Laura, I'll give this to you.

1438
01:13:43,981 --> 01:13:44,981
Thank you.

1439
01:13:45,381 --> 01:13:48,291
(Rolling the well-made rice ball in the sauce)

1440
01:13:48,691 --> 01:13:51,020
(Coating it nicely...)

1441
01:13:51,021 --> 01:13:52,891
(and then, taking a bite)

1442
01:13:53,231 --> 01:13:54,331
It's tasty.

1443
01:13:54,831 --> 01:13:56,861
Goodness. It's amazing with the sauce.

1444
01:13:58,701 --> 01:14:02,471
(He coats it with the sauce as he heard it tasted good.)

1445
01:14:03,071 --> 01:14:05,571
(Taking a bite of the rice ball dipped in the sauce)

1446
01:14:06,011 --> 01:14:07,141
Look.

1447
01:14:07,411 --> 01:14:08,671
May I suggest something?

1448
01:14:09,011 --> 01:14:10,681
Let's add all the rice to the sauce.

1449
01:14:11,241 --> 01:14:12,711
(Laughing)

1450
01:14:12,811 --> 01:14:13,880
(Why not?)

1451
01:14:13,881 --> 01:14:15,211
Let's pour the rice into the sauce.

1452
01:14:15,751 --> 01:14:17,820
No, we have to make rice balls.

1453
01:14:17,821 --> 01:14:20,151
We tried making them, so it's all good.

1454
01:14:20,221 --> 01:14:23,221
(A rule follower versus a rule breaker)

1455
01:14:23,761 --> 01:14:25,491
- Should we pour the rice into it? - Do it.

1456
01:14:25,831 --> 01:14:27,791
(They have similar taste buds.)

1457
01:14:28,091 --> 01:14:31,001
(Adding all of the rice balls to the pan)

1458
01:14:31,131 --> 01:14:32,971
(Scraping)

1459
01:14:33,501 --> 01:14:36,341
(Totally separated)

1460
01:14:36,671 --> 01:14:38,370
Guys, look at this.

1461
01:14:38,371 --> 01:14:39,841
Look how good it looks.

1462
01:14:41,141 --> 01:14:42,811
(Amazed)

1463
01:14:43,741 --> 01:14:45,511
This is Korean style.

1464
01:14:47,851 --> 01:14:49,380
You know it very well.

1465
01:14:49,381 --> 01:14:50,921
(They turned the rice balls into fried rice.)

1466
01:14:51,221 --> 01:14:53,191
When Koreans see us,

1467
01:14:54,091 --> 01:14:56,391
they'll probably say we're on top of everything.

1468
01:14:59,431 --> 01:15:01,961
They'll give us the Genius Award.

1469
01:15:03,061 --> 01:15:06,471
(We present them with the Food Genius Award.)

1470
01:15:07,031 --> 01:15:10,301
(Current time: 9pm)

1471
01:15:10,801 --> 01:15:12,771
It's sad to finish eating.

1472
01:15:13,741 --> 01:15:15,641
The chicken was delicious.

1473
01:15:16,341 --> 01:15:18,481
The rice balls were tasty and had a hint of seaweed.

1474
01:15:19,311 --> 01:15:20,680
Not bad.

1475
01:15:20,681 --> 01:15:21,751
I agree.

1476
01:15:22,051 --> 01:15:25,591
(They finished the meal satisfied.)

1477
01:15:26,891 --> 01:15:28,151
Are you all finished?

1478
01:15:28,351 --> 01:15:29,921
- Yes, we are. - Okay.

1479
01:15:30,121 --> 01:15:32,121
May I clear your plates?

1480
01:15:32,331 --> 01:15:33,331
Yes, of course.

1481
01:15:33,691 --> 01:15:34,691
(Actually, on Yu Ri's arm...)

1482
01:15:34,692 --> 01:15:35,930
We can serve desserts now, right?

1483
01:15:35,931 --> 01:15:37,501
Yes. I should clear the table.

1484
01:15:38,731 --> 01:15:41,001
(Before they open)

1485
01:15:41,771 --> 01:15:44,771
(She wrote some French phrases for serving...)

1486
01:15:45,001 --> 01:15:49,481
(on her arm as a cheat sheet.)

1487
01:15:53,311 --> 01:15:57,851
(Densely packed cheat sheet)

1488
01:15:58,251 --> 01:16:00,020
The waitress is adorable.

1489
01:16:00,021 --> 01:16:01,551
She had writings on her arm.

1490
01:16:01,591 --> 01:16:03,891
(Pausing as Yu Ri approaches)

1491
01:16:09,161 --> 01:16:11,561
She wrote phrases on her arm and read them.

1492
01:16:11,931 --> 01:16:13,631
To say "Did you enjoy it?"

1493
01:16:13,731 --> 01:16:16,101
And it was written in Korean.

1494
01:16:16,971 --> 01:16:19,341
So, she's reading Korean...

1495
01:16:19,811 --> 01:16:22,271
- That's so cute. - while trying to pronounce French.

1496
01:16:22,641 --> 01:16:23,681
That's really adorable.

1497
01:16:26,281 --> 01:16:28,710
(Yu Ri reviews them whenever she has a chance.)

1498
01:16:28,711 --> 01:16:31,651
- Is Table 2 ready? - Yes. Get ready for Table 2.

1499
01:16:32,591 --> 01:16:33,651
Have you set the table?

1500
01:16:35,921 --> 01:16:37,921
Are you filming "Memento" right now?

1501
01:16:41,531 --> 01:16:42,901
That's a good idea, though.

1502
01:16:43,061 --> 01:16:44,300
Nice, Yu Ri.

1503
01:16:44,301 --> 01:16:45,301
(Come to think of it, it's actually brilliant.)

1504
01:16:45,901 --> 01:16:48,600
I have to do this to say it, otherwise I just can't.

1505
01:16:48,601 --> 01:16:50,371
(Yu Ri is just built differently.)

1506
01:16:50,571 --> 01:16:52,910
- See you again. Yes. - Next time.

1507
01:16:52,911 --> 01:16:54,541
- Thank you. - Thanks.

1508
01:16:55,171 --> 01:16:58,741
(The guests leave one by one.)

1509
01:16:58,941 --> 01:17:01,081
(Only one table remains.)

1510
01:17:01,711 --> 01:17:03,221
How many cucumbers do we have?

1511
01:17:04,221 --> 01:17:05,421
- Cucumbers? - Yes.

1512
01:17:06,051 --> 01:17:07,450
Will you wash some cucumbers?

1513
01:17:07,451 --> 01:17:08,991
About ten of them.

1514
01:17:11,621 --> 01:17:12,690
Hold on.

1515
01:17:12,691 --> 01:17:14,931
(John comes in, brining back the plates to clean.)

1516
01:17:18,701 --> 01:17:21,531
What are you going to do with it?

1517
01:17:22,101 --> 01:17:23,901
- You can go. - Are we not going to go home?

1518
01:17:27,071 --> 01:17:29,010
(Sighing deliberately and noticeably)

1519
01:17:29,011 --> 01:17:30,110
Why did you sigh?

1520
01:17:30,111 --> 01:17:31,781
It doesn't feel like we're shooting a show anymore.

1521
01:17:32,651 --> 01:17:33,711
This is...

1522
01:17:34,251 --> 01:17:35,951
- an insufferable documentary. - Seriously.

1523
01:17:36,521 --> 01:17:38,121
How could this be a variety show?

1524
01:17:39,191 --> 01:17:42,491
What was the show where stars tried out various jobs?

1525
01:17:42,721 --> 01:17:46,161
It's like "Scenes! The Experience of Life" out there.

1526
01:17:46,761 --> 01:17:48,091
"Scenes! The Experience of Life?"

1527
01:17:49,201 --> 01:17:51,131
Wait. It's "Experience! The Scenes of Life"

1528
01:17:52,301 --> 01:17:54,301
- Thank you. - Thank you.

1529
01:17:54,571 --> 01:17:55,770
Thank you.

1530
01:17:55,771 --> 01:17:56,970
- Bye. - Thank you.

1531
01:17:56,971 --> 01:17:58,300
Well done, everyone.

1532
01:17:58,301 --> 01:17:59,840
- Well done. - Well done.

1533
01:17:59,841 --> 01:18:01,941
(So, how much did they make?)

1534
01:18:02,888 --> 01:18:04,717
(The Saturday rush begins.)

1535
01:18:04,718 --> 01:18:06,157
(To reach the highest sales ever,)

1536
01:18:06,158 --> 01:18:07,958
(Chef Paik tries something new.)

1537
01:18:08,388 --> 01:18:09,788
(Do you know how to make sulppang, the makgeolli bread?)

1538
01:18:10,358 --> 01:18:13,998
(In France, the country of bread,)

1539
01:18:15,758 --> 01:18:18,768
(they'll face it head-on with makgeolli bread!)

1540
01:18:18,828 --> 01:18:21,698
(However...)

1541
01:18:21,768 --> 01:18:22,908
I think it's the bread.

1542
01:18:23,938 --> 01:18:25,168
(Surprised)

1543
01:18:25,608 --> 01:18:28,408
(Is there a problem with the makgeolli bread?)

1544
01:18:28,978 --> 01:18:32,178
(On top of that, the customers rush out.)

1545
01:18:32,918 --> 01:18:35,618
(And an employee runs away?)

1546
01:18:35,918 --> 01:18:37,718
(She threw something and went out.)

1547
01:18:38,318 --> 01:18:43,328
(Is the business becoming a mess?)

1548
01:18:44,428 --> 01:18:48,028
(What on earth is happening to the Single Pan House?)
